reviewText: Awesome!  My 2 year old adores Yo Gabba Gabba.  Every dvd we purchase is always awesome!  She loves to sing along and dance!  And, she is learning how to be nice to her friends!!

Love Yo Gabba Gabba! Can the next DVD release please be 16x9 format instead of 4:3? It's 2011!
Everybody has widescreen TVs.

My 18 month old son loves Yo Gabba Gabba.  The songs are wonderful and the messages are great too.  On this DVD they stress the importance of washing your hands, wearing seat belts, going to the doctor and more.

We are a house hold that LOVES Gabba!  We are also a house hold that loves Anthony Bourdain. It was an episode that my daughter and mommy and daddy could watch! This DVD also has the older episodes too! Car, Teeth, and Clean are all on this DVD.  EVERY YO GABBA GABBA DVD comes with 4 episodes!

I had a Day Care and this one was one of our favorites.

Once I saw Anthony Bourdain as "the doctor", I knew I would love this DVD. My daughter loves the singing and dancing but I get a kick out of the other things she doesn't really notice. My husband and I are in healthcare so each episode is right up our alley; from the song about eating a BRAT (bananas, rice, applesauce, toast) diet when you're sick to washing your hands. This DVD is a winner!
Our son is so entertained by this dvd. I hate that I have to watch it over and over again but at least the songs are kind of catchy for me too.

I have 2 grandchildren who are addicted to Yo Gabba Gabba. They kept asking and asking for it so I bought a few on DVD and that did the trick. Altho now we have Amazon Prime and all of Season 1 is there and you can buy other seasons. I'm happy!

My kids love these shows, (I will admit, as the grown up, I do too!).  They have a lot of fun dancing and singing to the songs, it teaches them a lot of life lessons that are easy for two year olds to catch onto. Lot's of fun!

My 2 year old daughter loves this show. Recently, Netflix cut the show from their instantly watch list and My daughter watches nothing else. When she took it out the box she started dancing for joy. Making her happy makes us happy.
my daughter loves this show.  I personally can't stand it, but she's two and she absolutely loves the characters!  This is a must buy for any toddler!
A good resource to use when it's time to go to the doctor. Also, a good time to share with the grandkids that Gramma doesn't much like going there, either!
The DVD works great in our DVD player and the quality is good. 4 episodes on the DVDE which is nice!
A must have for any Gabba enthusiast to put in  your car DVD or watch when Gabba isn't on. These videos are a good value and well watched by any Gabba fan.
